# Duplicate Steps Detection

## Overview

The Duplicate Steps Detection rule identifies Cucumber step definitions that are defined multiple times, either as exact duplicates or as the same text with different step types. This helps prevent conflicts and maintain clean, non-redundant step definitions.

## Purpose

- **Conflict Prevention**: Avoid step definition conflicts that can cause test failures
- **Code Cleanliness**: Remove redundant step definitions
- **Maintenance**: Simplify step definition management
- **Clarity**: Prevent confusion from duplicate steps

## What Gets Detected

### Duplicate Types
- ✅ **Exact Duplicates**: Same type and text (e.g., two `When` steps with identical text)
- ✅ **Text Duplicates**: Same text with different types (e.g., `When` and `Then` with same text)
- ✅ **Cross-file Duplicates**: Same step defined in multiple files
- ✅ **Same-file Duplicates**: Multiple definitions in the same file

### Step Definition Patterns
- ✅ `Given('step text', function)` - String-based step definitions
- ✅ `When(/regex pattern/, function)` - Regex-based step definitions
- ✅ `Then('I should see {string}', function)` - Parameterized steps
- ✅ `And('step text', function)` - And/But step definitions
- ✅ Multi-line step definitions with complex patterns

## Cross-Project Duplicates (Allowed)

**Important**: Duplicate steps are **allowed and ignored** when they exist in different project folders:
- `core-app/` - Core application tests
- `webTv/` - WebTV application tests
- `operator-tool/` - Operator tool tests

### Why This Is Allowed
Each project maintains **independent test suites** and may intentionally have duplicate step definitions to:
- Maintain project independence
- Avoid cross-project dependencies
- Allow separate deployment and testing
- Enable team autonomy

### Example (Valid)
```javascript
// ✅ ALLOWED - Same step in different projects

// File: core-app/step-definitions/home.steps.js
Given('I launch the MLB.TV app', async function () {
  await browser.url('');
});

// File: webTv/features/step-definitions/common.steps.js
Given('I launch the MLB.TV app', async function () {
  await browser.url('');
});
```

**These duplicates will NOT be flagged** because they exist in different project folders.

### When Duplicates Are Flagged
Duplicates are **only flagged** when they exist:
- ✅ Within the same project folder (e.g., two steps in `core-app/`)
- ✅ Within the same file
- ✅ In non-project-specific locations

## Detection Logic

### 1. Step Definition Extraction
The rule scans all JavaScript files in `**/step-definitions/**/*.js` directories and extracts:
- Step text/pattern
- Step type (Given/When/Then/And/But)
- File location and line number
- Whether it's a regex or string-based step

### 2. Duplicate Grouping
The rule groups step definitions by:
- **Exact duplicates**: Same `type:text` combination
- **Text duplicates**: Same text regardless of type
- **File-based grouping**: Groups by file to identify same-file duplicates

### 3. Duplicate Classification
Each duplicate is classified as:
- **Exact duplicate**: Same type and text
- **Text duplicate**: Same text, different types
- **Same file**: Multiple definitions in same file
- **Cross file**: Same step in different files

## Examples

### ❌ BAD - Duplicate Step Definitions

```javascript
// Exact duplicate - same type and text
When('I click on the submit button', async function () {
  await $('button[type="submit"]').click();
});

When('I click on the submit button', async function () {
  await $('button[type="submit"]').click();
});

// Text duplicate - same text, different types
When('I navigate to the Home page', async function () {
  await browser.url('/home');
});

Then('I navigate to the Home page', async function () {
  await browser.url('/home');
});

// Regex duplicate - same pattern
When(/^I enter "([^"]*)" into the "([^"]*)" field$/, async function (value, field) {
  await $(`[name="${field}"]`).setValue(value);
});

When(/^I enter "([^"]*)" into the "([^"]*)" field$/, async function (value, field) {
  await $(`[name="${field}"]`).setValue(value);
});
```

### ✅ GOOD - Unique Step Definitions

```javascript
// Unique steps - no duplicates
Given('I launch the MLB.TV app', async function () {
  await browser.url('');
});

When('I click on the submit button', async function () {
  await $('button[type="submit"]').click();
});

Then('I should see the success message', async function () {
  await expect($('.success')).toBeDisplayed();
});

// Different text - not duplicates
When('I click on the submit button', async function () {
  await $('button[type="submit"]').click();
});

When('I click on the cancel button', async function () {
  await $('button[type="cancel"]').click();
});
```

## Real-World Examples

### Same Text, Different Types
```javascript
// File: core-app/step-definitions/settings.steps.js
When('I navigate to the Home page', async function () {
  await to_home();
});

Then('I navigate to the Home page', async function () {
  await to_home();
});
```
**Issue**: Same text with different step types (When vs Then)

### Exact Duplicates
```javascript
// File: operator-tool/step-definitions/common.steps.js
When('I click on the submit button', async function () {
  await $('button[type="submit"]').click();
});

// File: operator-tool/step-definitions/forms.steps.js  
When('I click on the submit button', async function () {
  await $('button[type="submit"]').click();
});
```
**Issue**: Exact same step defined in multiple files

### Regex Duplicates
```javascript
// File: step-definitions/login.steps.js
When(/^I enter "([^"]*)" into the "([^"]*)" field$/, async function (value, field) {
  await $(`[name="${field}"]`).setValue(value);
});

// File: step-definitions/forms.steps.js
When(/^I enter "([^"]*)" into the "([^"]*)" field$/, async function (value, field) {
  await $(`[name="${field}"]`).setValue(value);
});
```
**Issue**: Same regex pattern defined multiple times

## Manual Fix Process

To fix duplicate steps:

1. **Identify duplicate steps** from the check output
2. **Keep first occurrence** (by line number)
3. **Manually remove duplicate occurrences** from their files
4. **Handle file cleanup** if files become empty
5. **Verify fixes** by running the check again

### Fix Process
```bash
# Check for duplicate steps
npm run cursor-rules-check

# Manually review and remove duplicate step definitions
# Then verify fixes
npm run cursor-rules-check
```

### Fix Strategy
- **Keep first occurrence**: Preserves the step that appears first in the file
- **Remove duplicates**: Deletes subsequent occurrences
- **Maintain functionality**: Ensures remaining step still works
- **Clean up files**: Removes empty files if needed

## Special Cases

### Cross-File Duplicates
When the same step is defined in multiple files:
- **Keep all files**: Don't remove cross-file duplicates automatically
- **Manual review**: Requires human decision on which to keep
- **Consolidation**: May need to consolidate into shared file

### Same-File Duplicates
When multiple definitions exist in the same file:
- **Keep first**: Preserves the first occurrence
- **Remove rest**: Deletes subsequent duplicates
- **Line-based**: Uses line number to determine order

### Different Types, Same Text
When same text has different step types:
- **Keep one type**: Choose the most appropriate type
- **Update features**: Ensure feature files use correct type
- **Consolidate**: Merge into single step definition

## Best Practices

### 1. Step Organization
- **Single definition**: Define each step only once
- **Shared steps**: Use common step files for shared steps
- **File structure**: Organize steps by feature/functionality
- **Naming consistency**: Use consistent step naming

### 2. Step Types
- **Choose appropriate type**: Use Given/When/Then appropriately
- **Consistent usage**: Use same type across features
- **Avoid mixing**: Don't use different types for same action
- **Document conventions**: Establish team standards

### 3. Maintenance
- **Regular checks**: Run cursor rules frequently
- **Review duplicates**: Manually review cross-file duplicates
- **Consolidate steps**: Merge similar steps when appropriate
- **Update features**: Ensure features use correct step types

### 4. Prevention
- **Code reviews**: Check for duplicates in PRs
- **Automated checks**: Run cursor rules in CI/CD
- **Team communication**: Coordinate step definitions
- **Documentation**: Document step naming conventions

